THE GAME
--------

  'Simonize' is a Workbench game based on the old Simon game,
where you try to repeat a sequence of patterns (numbers or
whatever else) made by the computer. When you imitate that
sequence, the computer adds a new pattern and you must repeat
the same sequence and so on...

  This game adds a new twist to the game, instead of colours or
numbers, it displays a game board with a certain number of tiles,
depending on the game board size you want to play with.

  When the game starts, 'Simonize' will briefly highlight a
sequence of 3 tiles, and it's up to you to click on the right
tiles, in the same order. If you are successful, the game will
highlight those same tiles plus a new one and so on.

  The question is: can you successfully reproduce a sequence of
250 tiles?!

  Have fun!

